      <h1 class='title'>UK Gilts</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 c22WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_22ws' title='Col. 22WS &mdash; HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 c22WS' name='column_22ws' href='#column_22ws' rel='bookmark'>22WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0409P0-02339'>
        <a name='S6CV0409P0_20030715_CWS_22'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-healey' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0409P0_20030715_CWS_22' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Healey' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-healey" title="Mr John Healey">The Economic Secretary to the Treasury (John Healey)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0409P0-02339">The Bank of England's Registrar's Department has conducted gilts registration services on behalf of Her Majesty's Treasury to date, but will cease to do so from March 2005. A new service provider will need to be appointed to take its place. In preparing for outsourcing this service, the Government have taken the opportunity to modernise the arrangements for the registration and transfer of gilts. The re-engineered model has now been finalised, taking into account comments received in response to a recent consultation exercise. Details of the model are being deposited in the Libraries of both Houses today.</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02340">We plan to put the gilts registration service out to tender over the summer.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
